hether the existing build picks up the current build.gradle automatically. It seems like existing tests for version 2.1.7 are copied, while tests for 2.9.1 might be regenerated. The prompt mentions preparing a deterministic setup for a library issue, so I need to check if system properties like --add-opens are necessary beyond the normal scaffold.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing Guice coverage**\\n\\nI’m thinking about achieving meaningful coverage of Guice internals, like the enhancer and proxy. If there are no opens, Guice might resort to using Unsafe fallback. I’ve noticed that with the older CGLIB, there's a risk of running into InaccessibleObjectExceptions. It might be helpful to run a quick isolated test. Perhaps I could create a temporary directory in /tmp for Gradle to handle this? It seems like a good way to check my assumptions!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing Java dependencies**\\n\\nI'm working with Java and considering accessing jar dependencies from the Gradle cache. I might need to download transitive dependencies like aopalliance/javax.inject. It seems I could run tests using a simple injection and AOP. I want to make sure to use the 2.9.1 jar. Also, I should check if I need to compile with the current JDK. Alright, let me script something for a temporary javac setup!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_LsrAcRiYAtwRmElcusTgnzq8|fc_081672b95d893f6a016a41f07b62308196afc5fba967803b29", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport os, urllib.request\nbase='/tmp/sisu-guice-research'\ncoords=[('javax.inject','javax.inject','1'),('aopalliance','aopalliance','1.0')]\nfor g,a,v in coords:\n path=f'{base}/{a}-{v}.jar'\n if not os.path.exists(path):\n  url='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/'+g.replace('.','/')+'/'+a+'/'+v+'/'+a+'-'+v+'.jar'\n  urllib.request.urlretrieve(url,path)\nprint('done')\nPY\ncat > /tmp/sisu-guice-research/TestGuice.java <<'JAVA'\nimport com.google.inject.*;\nimport org.aopalliance.intercept.*;\nimport com.google.inject.matcher.Matchers;\n\npublic class TestGuice {\n  static class Dep { String value(){ return \"ok\"; } }\n  static class Target { @Inject Dep dep; public String call(){ return dep.value(); } }\n  static class Mod extends AbstractModule { protected void configure(){ bindInterceptor(Matchers.any(), Matchers.annotatedWith(Deprecated.class), new MethodInterceptor(){ public Object invoke(MethodInvocation inv) throws Throwable { return inv.proceed(); }}); } }\n  public static void main(String[] args) {\n    Injector injector = Guice.createInjector(new Mod());\n    Target target = injector.getInstance(Target.class);\n    System.out.println(target.call());\n  }\n}\nJAVA\ncd /tmp/sisu-guice-research\nCP=sisu-guice-2.9.1.jar:javax.inject-1.jar:aopalliance-1.0.jar\njavac -cp \"$CP\" TestGuice.java && echo '--- no opens ---' && java -cp \".:$CP\" TestGuice && echo '--- with opens ---' && java --add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED -cp \".:$CP\" TestGuice", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3437, "output": 1038, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24443, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782706287012, "responseId": "resp_081672b95d893f6a016a41f06f919c819682453eaa272d30da"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_LsrAcRiYAtwRmElcusTgnzq8|fc_081672b95d893f6a016a41f07b62308196afc5fba967803b29", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "done\n--- no opens ---\nException in thread \"main\" com.google.inject.internal.util.$ComputationException: com.google.inject.internal.util.$ComputationException: com.google.inject.internal.util.$ComputationException: java.lang.ExceptionInInitializerError\n\tat com.google.inject.internal.util.$MapMaker$StrategyImpl.compute(MapMaker.java:553)\n\tat com.google.inject.internal.util.$MapMaker$Stra